üìñ The Story of Ewelme Brook

The Ewelme Brook flows through the Thames & S. Chilterns catchment, where our eDNA survey sampled 8 sites along its length. Analysis of water samples revealed a rich invertebrate community with 4,803 distinct genetic sequences (ESVs) representing 558 identified species and 224 families.

Compared to other chalk streams surveyed, the Ewelme Brook shows moderate diversity compared to other rivers in the study (#6 of 10). The river supports 14 families of mayflies, stoneflies, and caddisflies (EPT) - key indicators of water quality.

Notable findings include the detection of conservation priority species (Water vole, Water shrew) and invasive species requiring management attention.
